==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ionophore
<hw>i*on"o*phore`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>ion</ets> +
<ets>-phore</ets>]</ety> <fld>(Biochemistry)</fld> <def>A compound that
enhances transport of ions across cellular membranes, by binding them
and carrying them across. As a class <ex>ionophores</ex> tend to be
lipophilic in nature; each compound is usually specific for one or a
small number of ions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

